sentences: Susannah Melvoin (born January 26, 1964) is an American vocalist and songwriter.
Prince wrote The Family's 1985 song "Nothing Compares 2 U" about Melvoin.
It charted when Sinéad O'Connor covered it in 1990.
Melvoin later joined the expanded line-up of The Revolution – adding backing vocals to Parade including the 1986 single "Anotherloverholenyohead."
